  "27": {
    "inputs": {
      "value": "A hard-boiled film-noir detective scene, but every element is rendered as handmade stop-motion claymation with visible fingerprint texture and seams in the modeling clay. A trench-coated clay detective with a lumpy fedora and a tiny clay cigarette stands under a flickering neon sign in a rain-slicked cyberpunk alley, holograms and Japanese signage glowing above. His clay face is half-lit, one eyebrow exaggeratedly raised. Beside him, a clay android informant with mismatched glowing LED eyes leans against a dumpster. Puddles of glossy clay-water reflect the magenta and cyan neon, raindrops sculpted as little clay teardrops frozen mid-fall. A clay cat watches from a fire escape. Moody high-contrast side lighting, deep blue shadows cut by hot neon rim light, volumetric clay \"fog.\" Shot on a 35mm lens, f/2.8, shallow depth of field with a tilt-shift miniature look, ISO 400. The slightly soft, saturated tonality of Cinestill 800T with its halated neon glow. Tactile, handmade, gritty yet charming."
    },
